Problem 1- Iron Bank

NULL HYPOTHESIS: Over the long run, securities trades from the Iron Bank are flagged at the same 2.4% baseline rate as that of other traders. We are testing if the observed data that states 70 flagged trades out of 2021 are consistent with the SECs null hypothesis.

TEST STATISTIC: The test statsitic used to measure evidence against the null hypothesis is 70

P-VALUE: The p-value is approximately 0.00189

CONCLUSION: Based on the calculated test statistic of 0.00189 being less than 0.05, the null hypothesis proves that in light of the data to be statisitcally signinficant. Meaning that the null hypothesis should be rejected. So, the staememnt that the Iron Bank are flagged at the same 2.4% baseline rate as that of other traders is false.

Problem 2- Health Inspections

We are testing if the observed data for 8 health code violations out of 50 remains the same. TEST STATISTIC: The test statistic used to measure evidence against the null hypothesis is 8.

P-VALUE: The p-value is approximately 0.00016

CONCLUSION: Based on the calculated test statistic of 0.00016 being less than 0.05, the null hypothesis proves that in light of the data, to be statistically significant.
